<L>__{interior hotel room. later.}
<A>__{jamal and latika lie on the bed, drunk, though still coherent. latika is dressed in the bell boy's jacket and the old lunghi.}
<C>__{latika}
<D>__{maman's gang will hunt us. you know that?}
<C>__{jamal}
<D>__{i don't care.}
<C>__{latika}
<D>__{me neither.}
<A>__{they burst into stupid laughter. the laughter subsides.}
<C>__{jamal}
<D>__{that dance you were doing. in pila street. show me.}
<A>__{latika rolls over and switches off the light. rolls back. in the half light, her hands begin to move for jamal, the elegant, alluring hand movements of the bar girl dancers. jamal stares, mesmerised.}
<C>__{latika}
<D>__{you came back for me.}
<C>__{jamal}
<D>__{of course.}
<C>__{latika}
<D>__{i thought you'd forgotten.}
<C>__{amir}
<D>__{i never forgot. not for one day. i knew i'd find you in the end. it's our destiny.}
<C>__{latika}
<D>__{destiny. yes.}
<A>__{latika stops her hands. they stare at each other, their faces inches away from each other. latika strokes jamal's face.}
<C>__{latika }
<D>__{thank you.}
<A>__{and face to face, they slowly fall asleep.}
